<P ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT SIZE="-1" COLOR="GREEN"><I>Rig Veda</I>, tr. by Ralph T.H. Griffith, [1896], at sacred-texts.com</FONT></P><HR></p>  <h3 align="center" align="center">HYMN CLXXXVI. V&#257;yu.</h3>  
<p>1. FILLING our hearts with health and joy, may V&#257;ta breathe his balm on us<br> May he prolong our days of life.<br> 2 Thou art our Father, V&#257;ta, yea, thou art a Brother and a friend,<br> So give us strength that we may live.<br> 3 The store of Am&#7771;ta laid away yonder, O V&#257;ta, in thine home,&#151;<br> Give us thereof that we may live.</p>  
